<subSubSection id="C32B6510FFABFFC4FF385F3623B02A37" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8E369BFFABFFC4FF385F3623422874" blockId="1.[151,465,223,286]" box="[151,336,259,286]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FF385F3622B22877" bold="true" box="[151,160,259,285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">(</emphasis>
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FF0E5F3622FF2877" box="[161,237,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FF545F36231B2877" box="[251,265,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FE825F31235A2874" box="[301,328,260,286]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,1124,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-38@7.[253,1334,1123,1955]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Basal portion of male antenna, dorsal view, color photographs. a. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n.; b. Rhopalopsole yadonga sp. n.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504184/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">7a</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8E369BFFABFFC4FF385F7E215F28BB" blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FF385F7E22C9280F" bold="true" box="[151,219,331,357]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Male.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity id="4CC99B7EFFABFFC4FE095F7E23EC280C" box="[422,510,331,358]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
(n=2). Head (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FD0E5F7E20E3280F" box="[673,753,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
) brown, occiput light brown, slightly wider than pronotum; compound eyes black; antennae (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FDBC5F5A207628E0" box="[531,612,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1979,2003]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,1124,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-38@7.[253,1334,1123,1955]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Basal portion of male antenna, dorsal view, color photographs. a. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n.; b. Rhopalopsole yadonga sp. n.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504184" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504184/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Fig. 7a</figureCitation>
) light brown, scape brown, without long hairs. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FAA95F5A274428E3" box="[1286,1366,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
) light brown, surface with brown regularly shaped longitudinal stripes, corners rounded; wings membrane pale brown hyaline,veins grayish brown. Legs and abdomen light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8E369BFFABFFC4FF685FEE21772A53" blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">
Terminalia. Tergum 9 (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FE665FEE2031289F" box="[457,547,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1a</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FDE85FEE2071289F" box="[583,611,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2a</figureCitation>
) mostly sclerotized, mid-posterior margin forming a strongly sclerotized, rectangular band with triangular posteromedial apex. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FC6E5FCA260C2B73" box="[961,1054,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1b</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FBE95FCA26712B70" box="[1094,1123,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2b</figureCitation>
) of sternum 9 much longer than wide and rounded apically, basally with a tongue-like vesicle covered by dense hairs. Tergum 10 (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FA8B5C16276D2B57" box="[1316,1407,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1a</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FF385C7222A12B0B" box="[151,179,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2a</figureCitation>
) central plate bilobed, separated medially to form a pair of reniform sclerites, distal portions darker and covered with sensilla basiconica; transverse bars triangular with anterior edge strongly sclerotized. Lateral projections (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FACB5C5E22CE2BC3" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1c, 1d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FF485CBA23112BC3" box="[231,259,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2c</figureCitation>
) of tergum 10 short and sclerotized, generally triangular in dorsal/dorsolateral view and elliptical in lateral view. Cercus (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FE975C8623AD2BA7" box="[312,447,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1a–1d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FE645C86201D2BA7" box="[459,527,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2a–2c</figureCitation>
) slightly upcurved medially, without apical spine. Epiproct (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FB135C8627502BA7" box="[1212,1346,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1c, 1d</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FAE05C8627862BA7" box="[1359,1428,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2a, 2c</figureCitation>
) basally thick with erect, strongly sclerotized, hook-like, sharp apex in lateral view. Subanal lobe (
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FB705CE227772B9B" box="[1247,1381,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-32@2.[151,1436,181,1822]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), color photographs. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view; d. Terminalia, dorsolateral view; e. Head and pronotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504170" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504170/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Figs. 1b, 1c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="130A2A1EFFABFFC4FADD5CE222A62A7C" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1905,1929]" captionTargetBox="[163,1427,181,1870]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[151,1436,181,1882]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole liui sp. n. (male), line drawing. a. Terminalia, dorsal view; b. Terminalia, ventral view; c. Terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6504172" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6504172/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">2b– 2d</figureCitation>
) of large size, distinctly upturned distally, apex and lateral margins darkly sclerotized, covered by longitudinal furrows and with two dark forked projections in ventral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8E369BFFABFFC4FF685D7623B02A37" blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1258]" box="[199,418,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FF685D7623372A37" bold="true" box="[199,293,835,861]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
