<subSubSection id="C32B6510FFABFFC4FF685A2E23B12D83" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8E369BFFABFFC4FF685A2E23B12D83" blockId="1.[151,1437,331,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FF685A2E23292D5F" bold="true" box="[199,315,1051,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C314D18FFABFFC4FEEA5A2E201C2D5F" authorityName="Chen &amp; Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[325,526,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liui">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FEEA5A2E201C2D5F" box="[325,526,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Rhopalopsole liui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D18FFABFFC4FD515A2921BD2D5F" authorityName="Yang, D. &amp; C. Yang" authorityYear="1994" box="[766,943,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shaanxiensis">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FD515A2921BD2D5F" box="[766,943,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">R. shaanxiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B6AFFABFFC4FB895A2E26EF2D5F" author="Sivec, I. &amp; Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T." box="[1062,1277,1051,1077]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref3190" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T. (2008) Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia, 64, 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="2008">
Sivec 
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FBC15A2926BB2D5F" box="[1134,1193,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
with short or obsolete lateral projections of tergum 10 and large subanal lobes. The new species seems related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D18FFABFFC4FAB25A7523752D17" authority="(Sivec et al. 2008)" baseAuthorityName="Sivec" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qinlinga">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FAB25A75278E2D33" box="[1309,1436,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">R. qinlinga</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B6AFFABFFC4FF305A5623722D17" author="Sivec, I. &amp; Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T." box="[159,352,1123,1150]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref3190" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T. (2008) Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia, 64, 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="2008">
Sivec 
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FF495A51230A2D17" box="[230,280,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in having similar forked processes in ventral surface of subanal lobe, however, the central plate of 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D18FFABFFC4FF185AB2236C2DCB" authority="Chen &amp; Wang &amp; Li, 2022" authorityName="Chen &amp; Wang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[183,382,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="liui" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FF185AB2236C2DCB" box="[183,382,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">Rhopalopsole liui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27657F2FFABFFC4FE285ABD23CD2DC8" box="[391,479,1160,1186]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a pair of reniform sclerites and shorter lateral projections, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C314D18FFABFFC4FB5E5ABD277C2DCB" box="[1265,1390,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="qinlinga">
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FB5E5ABD277C2DCB" box="[1265,1390,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">R. qinlinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a narrow central plate and lateral projections of the 10 tergum being long and forked to acute apices (figs. 34.1 &amp; 34.2, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA04B6AFFABFFC4FF795AFA23862D83" author="Sivec, I. &amp; Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T." box="[214,404,1231,1258]" pageId="1" pageNumber="570" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref3190" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T. (2008) Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia, 64, 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="2008">
Sivec 
<emphasis id="B945EA89FFABFFC4FEB45AE5235F2D83" box="[283,333,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="570">et al</emphasis>
. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
